#!/usr/bin/env bun
/**
 * One-shot stub generator for the documentation IA.
 *
 * Reads the table below — one entry per IA page — and creates a
 * Starlight Markdown stub for each entry that doesn't already exist
 * on disk.  Already-existing files (e.g. the two migration guides
 * landed in Commit 2.1) are skipped so re-running the script is
 * idempotent.
 *
 * Each stub gets:
 *   - Minimal Starlight front-matter (title + description).
 *   - A short "under construction" body that points readers at the
 *     source code, the auto-generated API reference, and the README
 *     until the real concept guide is written.
 *
 * Re-run after changes to the table:
 *
 *   cd docs && bun scripts/scaffold.mjs
 *
 * The script only adds; it never overwrites an existing file.  Delete
 * the stub manually if you need to regenerate it from scratch.
 *
 * Pages are listed in IA-Part order (Part 1 → Part 12).  Within a
 * Part, the order matches the sidebar order we'll configure in
 * Commit 2.3.  Keep this list in sync with `astro.config.mjs`'s
 * sidebar config — both must agree on path + label.
 */
import * as fs from 'node:fs';
import * as path from 'node:path';

